HEADWORD: Trisected
<hw>Tri*sect"ed</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Divided into
three parts or segments by incisions extending to the midrib or to the
base; -- said of leaves.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trisection</ent>⟦br⟧
